of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Moray in northeastern Scotland, which derives from Celtic <i>mori-</i> ‘sea’ + <i>treb-</i> ‘settlement’. The founder of the Scottish house of Murray was a Fleming named Freskin who was granted Strathbrock in West Lothian and Duffus in Moray by David I. The family took its name from the region in the late 12th century.","Irish and Scottish: shortened form of   McMurray  .","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Muireadhaigh</b> ‘descendant of <i>Muireadhach</i>’ a personal name meaning ‘mariner’. Occasionally it may be a shortened form of   McMurray  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Murri","meanings":["Probably Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murry","meanings":["Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murrah","meanings":["Probably an altered form of Scottish   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Murie","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel.","Scottish: habitational name from Murie in Errol (Perthshire).","Scottish and Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"Merhi","meanings":["Arabic (mainly Lebanon and Syria): from a variant of the personal name <i>Mirhi</i> of unknown meaning. Bearers of this surname are both Muslims and Christians. Compare   Murray   5."]},{"name":"Murrey","meanings":["Irish: variant of   Murray  ."]},{"name":"McMurray","meanings":["Irish (northern) and Scottish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Muireadhaigh</b> or <b>Mac Muireadhaich</b>, a patronymic from the personal name <i>Muireadhach</i> ‘seafarer’ (see   Murdoch  ). Compare   McCurry   1."]},{"name":"Murra","meanings":["Italian (Sicily): topographic name from Sicilian <i>murra</i> ‘large rock, mass of rocks’ or a habitational name from a place called with this word.","East Frisian: unexplained.","Albanian: nickname from <i>murrë</i> (definite form <i>murra</i>) ‘dark gray cow’."]},{"name":"Murrie","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Murray  ."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Gaelic equivalent of <b>Adam</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Adam Murray was born about 1327, in Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, his father, William Murray - III Laird of Tullibardine, was 39 and his mother, Mabel Isabella Randolf, was 38. He married Mrs Adam Murray in 1351, in Dumfriesshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. He died in Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland."},"et":{"about 1327–":"umbes 1327–Surnud","1306–Male":"1306–Surnud","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1353–1388":"1353–1388","1357–Male":"1357–Surnud","1358–Male":"1358–Surnud","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1290–Female":"1290–Surnud","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1351":"1351","Abt 1357":"umbes 1357","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1347":"1347","1357":"1357","about 1327":"umbes 1327","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1353":"1353","1307":"1307","1306":"1306","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Cockpool, Annadale, Dumfries, Scotland":"Cockpool, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1327–":"noin 1327–Kuollut","1306–Male":"1306–Kuollut","1307–1347":"1307–1347","1310–1380":"1310–1380","1327–Male":"1327–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1353–1388":"1353–1388","1357–Male":"1357–Kuollut","1358–Male":"1358–Kuollut","1290–1352":"1290–1352","1290–Female":"1290–Kuollut","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1351":"1351","Abt 1357":"noin 1357","1380":"1380","1290":"1290","1327":"1327","1358":"1358","1347":"1347","1357":"1357","about 1327":"noin 1327","1388":"1388","1310":"1310","1353":"1353","1307":"1307","1306":"1306","Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Dumfriesshire, Scotland","Cockpool, Dumfriessh